OL,3,CTrade union threatens legal action
OL,4,Cover winter fuel cut
OL,6,FThe union said it believed the
OL,7,Fgovernment had breached its legal
OL,8,Fduties by not referring the cut to the
OL,9,FSocial Security Advisory Committee
OL,10,F(SSAC) and by failing to consider the
OL,11,Fimpact on disabled people, among other
OL,12,Fgrounds.
OL,14,FMinisters are not required to refer
OL,15,Fregulations on benefits to the SSAC if
OL,16,Fthey are a matter of "urgency",
OL,17,Fsomething the government relied on
OL,18,Fwhen implementing the winter fuel cut.
